      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i keep noticing something weird with my smart thermostat. every time i get really stressed or upset, the temp in the room drops like 3 or 4 degrees almost instantly. it's like it knows. i've checked the settings and there aren't any automation rules that would do this. is there any way these things are actually monitoring more than just the air temp?",
